Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Twelfth \Twelfth\, a. [For twelft, OE. twelfte, AS. twelfta. See {Twelve}.] 1. Next in order after the eleventh; coming after eleven others; -- the ordinal of twelve. [1913 Webster]
2. Consisting, or being one of, twelve equal parts into which anything is divided. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Twelfth \Twelfth\, n. 1. The quotient of a unit divided by twelve; one of twelve equal parts of one whole. [1913 Webster]
2. The next in order after the eleventh. [1913 Webster]
3. (Mus.) An interval comprising an octave and a fifth. [1913 Webster]
twelfth adj : coming next after the eleventh and just before the thirteenth in position [syn: {12th}] n : position 12 in a countable series of things
